  <section class="topic">
  <h3>Bridged vs NAT in Hypervisors</h3>
  <div class="grid two">
    <div>
      <h4>Overview</h4>
      <p>Compared NAT vs Bridged networking for VMs; validated IP assignment and reachability to LAN services.</p>
      <h4>Approach</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Created two VMs: one NAT, one Bridged</li>
        <li>Verified <code>ipconfig /all</code> / <code>ip a</code> and default routes</li>
        <li>Tested ping/DNS to LAN and Internet</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h4>Evidence</h4>
      <ul class="evidence">
        <li><a href="assets/images/2025-11-bridgednat-01.png" target="_blank">NAT vs Bridged IPs</a></li>
        <li><a href="assets/images/2025-11-bridgednat-02.png" target="_blank">Route table comparison</a></li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Reflection</h4>
      <p>Bridged is great for lab servers reachable from the LAN; NAT is safer for isolated testing. Documented when to use each.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

